<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MTA61">
<l>ulaku mulakiṟanta vūḻiyu moṇkēḻ</l>
<l>vilaku karuṅkaṭalum veṟpu – mulakiṉiṟ</l>
<l>centīyu mārutamum vāṉun, tirumāṟaṉ</l>
<l>puntiyi lāya puṇarppu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The world and the aeons, during which the world expires, and in the world</l>
<l>the receding<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">vilakutal is a rare verb with a possible primary meaning “to recede”, whereas the Vyākyānam glosses here by alai eṟiyāniṉṟa, “that kept dashing waves”, which would be the direct opposite; for the time being I cannot provide any obvious parallel.</note> black ocean with bright lustre, the mountains,</l>
<l>red fire, the wind and the sky are the creation</l>
<l>that comes into existence in the mind of Tirumāl.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
